Run with convert_automaton.rb can be given an automaton to convert via plain
stdin, or via redirecting a file into its stdin, or by giving a path to a file,
or by piping into it...

It really doesn't care. Go ahead and try it.

First though you'll have to 'gem install' 'oj' (and before that you might
have to install rubygems on your system, and before that you might have to
install Ruby...)
